Health Information Systems: Concepts, Methodologies, Tools, and Applications
Publisher: Medical Information Science Reference | ISBN: 1605669881 | edition 2009 | PDF | 2311 pages 

Health Information Systems: Concepts, Methodologies, Tools, and Applications provides a complete understanding of the development of applications and concepts in clinical, patient, and hospital information systems. This massive multi-volume reference addresses the demand for a resource that encompasses the most pertinent research in health information systems, healthcare technologies, and telemedicine.
